rehensive knowledge of Spanish cultural forms and traditions (esperpento, sainete costumbrista) with a detailed textual analysis of all of Álex de la Iglesia’s seven feature films.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAcción mutante.  aMuertos de risa.  aSpanish film.  aavant-garde.  acomedy.  adirector.  aesperpento.  ahorror.  apopular auteur.  asainete costumbrista.1 aBuse, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBuse, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aToribio, Núria Triana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTriana-Toribio, Nuria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWillis, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779166540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791665423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791665/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles